{
  "texts": [
    "This dynamically generated knowledge is particularly valuable because it is produced by LLMs, which draw on a broad and flexible understanding of language and commonsense, overcoming the limitations of static knowledge bases that may not cover all potential nonsensical concepts.",
    "Employing LLMs ensures that K is specific to the context of S and sufficiently general to cover a wide range of possible scenarios.",
    "By explicitly representing this knowledge, the explanation generation model will be better equipped to understand the underlying commonsense principles, thereby enabling it to generate more accurate and contextually appropriate explanations.",
    "Explanation generationOnce the implicit knowledge K has been generated, the next step is to use this knowledge to construct a prompt that will guide the LLM in generating the explanation Y.",
    "In this step, the grounded implicit knowledge helps the LLM understand why the nonsensical statement conflicts with commonsense, thereby enabling it to generate an output that clarifies the commonsense contradiction.The construction of the prompt involves incorporating K alongside the nonsensical statement S into a prompt template."
  ]
}